## §1 Terminal goal — real-semantics formal closure of 4 F-CL-FORMAL axes

The lean4 mechanical layer at `~/core/hexa-meta/formal/lean4/`
proves 4 closure-machinery theorems over hexa-bio's WEAVE composition.

| Axis | Theorem name | Statement | Status (2026-05-12 cycle-30) |
|------|--------------|-----------|---------------|
| F-CL-FORMAL-1 | `sigma_lattice_card` | `sigma 6 = 12` | **REAL-SEMANTICS PROVEN** (`sigma` is a computable Nat divisor-sum; `rfl`) |
| F-CL-FORMAL-2 | `landauer_monotonic` | `heatConsumed (compose kT s₁ s₂) ≥ max …` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v3** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++++, hexa-meta `9e44e75`; v2 baseline `2c68bea`) — kT now opaque positive ℝ via section variable + `[Fact (0 < kT)]` instance (was hard-coded `kT := 1` in v2). `landauerFloorPerBit kT = kT · Real.log 2` parametric; `landauerFloorPerBit_pos` uses `hkT.out`. All 3 bonus theorems (`landauer_pass_compose`, `landauer_pass_merge`, `landauer_pass_heat_nonneg`) thread kT through with byte-identical proof bodies; compose/merge get `omit hkT in` to silence linter (proofs don't consume positivity). Added `Mathlib.Logic.Basic` for `Fact`. v4 stretch: parametrise the entire energy substrate (`[OrderedAddCommGroup E]` instead of `ℝ`). |
| F-CL-FORMAL-3 | `pi_p2_verifier_terminates` | `∃ n, verifierSteps q ≤ n` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v3** (2026-05-12 cycle-30+++++, hexa-meta `2680f88`; v2 baseline `2c68bea`) — `verifierSteps q := verifierStepsRec c.size q.depth q.payload` where `verifierStepsRec` is RECURSIVE: base `sz + p`, step `2 * (recursive_call_at_depth-1)`. Terminates by Lean's automatic `Nat.rec` well-foundedness (`Nat.rec` IS the well-founded recursor — no explicit `WellFoundedRelation` instance needed). Closed-form characterisation `verifierStepsRec sz d p = 2^d * (sz + p)` kernel-checked via induction + `Nat.pow_succ` + `ring`. Witness updated to `2 ^ q.depth * (12 + q.payload)`. Bonus theorems: `verifierStepsRec_closed_form` (the v3↔closed-form link), `verifierSteps_mono_depth` (re-proved through closed-form), `two_pow_pos`, `verifierSteps_ge_v2_bound` (v3 cost ≥ v2 closed-form bound — v3 is strictly more pessimistic). Mathlib imports added: `Tactic.Linarith`, `Tactic.Ring`. v4 stretch: arbitrary measure function via `WellFoundedRelation`/`Prod.lex` (for verifiers whose decreasing measure is not depth alone). |
| F-CL-FORMAL-4 | `closure_cert_idempotent` | `∀ c : ClosureCert α [DecidableEq α], discloseTwice c = discloseOnce c` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v3** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++++, hexa-meta `9e44e75`; v2 baseline `350798c`) — `structure ClosureCert (α : Type) [DecidableEq α]`: `caveat_bag` / `signer_set` / `seal_caveats` / `seal_signers` all `Finset α` (was `Finset Nat` in v2); `payload`/`disclosed` unchanged. `discloseOnce` is a seal-on-first-disclosure operation (idempotent by `if_pos` on the `disclosed` flag). All 5 theorems re-proved with byte-identical proof bodies (same `by_cases h; simp [h]` patterns) — typeclass propagates through simp/Finset.insert without tactic adjustments. v4 stretch: parametrise caveat-payload semantics (`[CommutativeMonoid β]`) for richer disclosure operations. |

**v1 → v2 promotion DoD per axis** (cycle-30++): full WEAVE composition
algebra (sub-additive composition under reversible re-merge; real-valued
heat with `Real.log` + Mathlib SHA-pin; exponential-in-depth Π^p_2 worst
case; payload-level disclosure invariants) + Mathlib-backed proof bodies
+ sorry-count = 0 + machine-checked under `lake build`. The v1 → v2 work
is **NOT a v1.x closure blocker** — by design, the v1.x cert surrogate
is the `raw_91_c3_disclose:MVP_caveat` disclosure (per `.roadmap.weave`
line 21), and v1 PASS is the maximum formal-axis closure available in
the v1.x track.

